Petasma with broad, distally rounded lateral lobule, slightly to considerably surpassing median lobule; ventral costa unattached to adjacent flexible part for variable fraction of its length, and not produced into hook. First abdominal somite dorsally rounded; second and third somite dorsally rounded or very faint rounded carina; fourth to sixth somites dorsally carinate, carina of fourth somite extending along posterior two-thirds. Telson bearing four pairs of movable spines; apex acute, slender (modified from
Pérez Farfante & Kensley, 1997
).
